76561197981884925,Recommended,283100,10034196,"Posted: 6 May, 2014",all,gozz,"The game is still very early in development. So with that, the game is ""very basic"" and only leaves you with two options: Farm bugs or search for pvp.The game itself looks like it can be a great purchase in the long run, right now I can see some people being easily turned off, just because they have not made it user friendly (no options menu, no guide, and somewhat hard to figure out mapping system)I would recommend people to try out the game, but I would also recommend trying it with a friend. Going solo can be slow and frustrating, but rewarding. Grouping up with a friend added a different element as there is friendly fire in the game.To touch base on the pvp aspect, on the intial world there is no pvp and no construction, so you do not really have to worry about griefers. When you feel ready you can try going to the next planet. First you need to figure out how to travel (again no guides, but after asking in chat someone instructed me). You need to find and purchase a ILU (Individual Landing Unit) and select a planet, then select a sector on that planet to go to. Each sector is HUGE and there are over 10-15 sectors on each planet, so getting ganked repeatedly should not be an issue.Overall I am having fun with it.  I Suggest trying it out, but keep in mind that this game is still really young."
